column5: Went out this morning for a couple of hours with a good buddy of mine Mike (dozer).  We got down to the water around 7 am (it's starting to get cold).  Fortunately no one else around at the time.  First 30 minutes started off slow and them BAM!   Float down.  Between 7 and 10 am we caught 8 in total, Here's a few pictures of the more respectable ones.   Quality isn't the greatest (blackberry).  Enjoy
Sweet chromers! Thanks for sharing.  p.-
Good stuff, if only i hadnt had to work id be landing chrome like that
Nice work!  Gotta love it when a plan comes together
yeah Blackberry cameras are crap arent they ....but ....good enough to see the fish....nice shootin!
nice going - that last one is a beaut.
Those fishies are very shiny...almost got blinded staring at them
NICE JOB BRO!!--where were you fishing if you don't mind?
